{"questionId":"21926","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the function&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></math>. The graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> is shown in the diagram.&nbsp;The vertex of the graph has coordinates <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>−</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>)</mo></math>. The graph intersects the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis at&nbsp;two points, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mo>−</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/834f4780d263df96fc8275f7e67b2e6a0ca17e70.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the value of</p>\n<p>(i)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>(ii)&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>(iii)&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>b</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>b</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>25</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mi>a</